Ore is an educational x86_64 operating system.

Current focus:
- stable ring3 syscall ABI
- initramfs shell
- simple interactive environment

The roadmap is intentionally small and direct. First we keep the kernel honest:
clear syscall ABI, guarded user pointers, controlled page faults, process
metadata, and file handles with real offsets. Then the shell grows into a
small workspace with commands, docs, demos, and eventually an in-system
programming layer.

This file is deliberately longer than one userspace read buffer. It verifies
that open/read/close keep per-handle offsets instead of returning only the first
chunk of a file. If cat can print this whole paragraph, the VFS handle path is
already more useful than the first MVP shortcut.
